1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,700
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,700 --> 00:00:03,100
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,845 --> 00:00:07,645
I think you've got the wrong idea.

4
00:00:08,433 --> 00:00:10,213
I don't believe we've met.

5
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,232
What are you talking about?
You don't recognize me?

6
00:00:15,449 --> 00:00:18,405
It's me, Jeong Dong Pal.

7
00:00:20,896 --> 00:00:22,432
Dong Pal.

8
00:00:25,271 --> 00:00:27,616
We shared a room for five years...

9
00:00:29,266 --> 00:00:30,533
You've mistaken me for someone else.

10
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,300
(Episode 58)

11
00:00:36,573 --> 00:00:38,573
Honey. Seung Ri.

12
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:41,579
What's going on? Who's that?

13
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:45,800
I don't know.
I think he came looking for someone.

14
00:00:46,517 --> 00:00:47,517
What brings you here?

15
00:00:47,517 --> 00:00:50,509
I forgot some documents,
so Mom brought them to me.

16
00:00:51,209 --> 00:00:52,209
Really?

17
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:59,211
Looks like today isn't a good day.

18
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,000
I'll come back again soon.

19
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:12,581
Dad, are you okay?

20
00:01:12,973 --> 00:01:14,340
You look pale.

21
00:01:15,787 --> 00:01:17,587
No, I'm fine.

22
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:21,544
Want to grab a meal together somewhere?

23
00:01:22,115 --> 00:01:23,360
It's almost lunchtime.

24
00:01:24,973 --> 00:01:27,600
You two go ahead.
I've got a lot of work to do.

25
00:01:29,754 --> 00:01:30,979
What's with him?

26
00:01:32,147 --> 00:01:33,661
Your dad's acting strange today.

27
00:01:34,001 --> 00:01:35,001
Yeah.

28
00:01:37,994 --> 00:01:39,827
As a surprise...

29
00:01:46,916 --> 00:01:47,916
Hello.

30
00:01:49,496 --> 00:01:52,064
Team Manager Ko, long time no see.

31
00:01:52,267 --> 00:01:53,267
Yes.

32
00:01:54,833 --> 00:01:56,200
I'm Manager Seo's mother.

33
00:01:57,084 --> 00:01:59,027
You look a lot like your mother.

34
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:01,493
At first glance, I didn't realize it.

35
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:05,925
I saw you before, on the day
your mom had her line dancing class.

36
00:02:06,221 --> 00:02:07,803
Yes, I remember.

37
00:02:09,376 --> 00:02:12,248
If you have time, would you like
to have lunch together somewhere?

38
00:02:12,248 --> 00:02:14,595
I'm sorry, but we brought lunchboxes.

39
00:02:16,284 --> 00:02:17,363
- Lunchboxes?
- Yes.

40
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,784
I see. Enjoy your lunch, then.

41
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:25,633
Yes. See you next time.

42
00:02:35,863 --> 00:02:38,813
Get a grip.
Even after seeing that, you are...

43
00:02:44,632 --> 00:02:45,999
Son, it's me.

44
00:02:47,073 --> 00:02:48,600
I'm in the company lobby right now.

45
00:02:49,327 --> 00:02:50,781
Okay. I'll wait.

46
00:02:52,176 --> 00:02:53,888
Mom, please.

47
00:02:54,184 --> 00:02:55,891
Seriously, not anymore.

48
00:02:56,656 --> 00:02:59,504
Now that I've seen Gyeol with my own eyes,

49
00:02:59,947 --> 00:03:02,536
don't even bring him up again, okay?

50
00:03:05,654 --> 00:03:06,654
Hello.

51
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:09,800
Hey, you haven't eaten yet, have you?

52
00:03:10,721 --> 00:03:12,285
Then enjoy your meal.

53
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,739
Mom, the documents.

54
00:03:15,631 --> 00:03:16,631
Hey, Seo Seung Ri!

55
00:03:19,311 --> 00:03:21,834
I'm sorry, Mother.
I'll go talk to Seung Ri.

56
00:03:22,064 --> 00:03:24,243
I'll take you somewhere nice next time.

57
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,133
- Okay, go ahead.
- Yes.

58
00:03:29,915 --> 00:03:32,125
Seo Seung Ri, that fool.

59
00:03:32,809 --> 00:03:36,616
Why does she keep looking elsewhere
when the treasure's right beside her?

60
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,627
Seriously.

61
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,400
What's this?

62
00:03:43,247 --> 00:03:46,085
I secretly packed and decorated it myself.
What do you think?

63
00:03:46,557 --> 00:03:47,584
It's childish.

64
00:03:48,024 --> 00:03:49,960
Why? Don't insult my work like that.

65
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:53,052
Should we bring lunchboxes every day?

66
00:03:53,052 --> 00:03:54,640
I'll pack them every morning.

67
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:56,700
All I have to do
is put the side dishes in the containers.

68
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,763
No. Maybe once in a while,
but not every day.

69
00:03:59,136 --> 00:04:01,635
Seriously, read the room.

70
00:04:01,635 --> 00:04:02,752
Didn't I tell you?

71
00:04:02,971 --> 00:04:06,094
People aren't that interested
in other people's lives.

72
00:04:06,383 --> 00:04:08,240
Everyone's too busy
trying to make a living.

73
00:04:08,996 --> 00:04:11,021
Do you really like lunchboxes that much?

74
00:04:11,965 --> 00:04:14,440
Yes.
It feels like going on a picnic every day.

75
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:15,733
Do you like picnics?

76
00:04:18,076 --> 00:04:21,349
Actually, I didn't after I turned seven.

77
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,233
But now I do again.

78
00:04:23,617 --> 00:04:25,155
After seven? Why?

79
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:28,085
Maybe I hit puberty early.

80
00:04:33,919 --> 00:04:35,317
This braised beef is really good.

81
00:04:35,488 --> 00:04:36,848
It tastes just like my grandma's.

82
00:04:37,321 --> 00:04:39,037
Her cooking was amazing.

83
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:42,803
Your house is completely different
from what I imagined...

84
00:04:42,803 --> 00:04:44,152
a rich chairman's house would be like.

85
00:04:44,412 --> 00:04:45,412
In what way?

86
00:04:45,669 --> 00:04:47,939
You know how in dramas,
there are rows of maids...

87
00:04:47,939 --> 00:04:50,395
in uniforms standing behind them
while they eat?

88
00:04:51,221 --> 00:04:52,765
Just watching that gives me indigestion.

89
00:04:54,311 --> 00:04:55,912
But your house...

90
00:04:56,143 --> 00:04:58,549
isn't really that different
from my ordinary home.

91
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,400
Your grandmother does the cooking herself.

92
00:05:02,624 --> 00:05:04,176
I think your grandparents...

93
00:05:04,176 --> 00:05:06,243
are both so kind and warm.

94
00:05:06,641 --> 00:05:09,781
I'll be sure to tell them
that you've completely fallen for them.

95
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:11,520
I wasn't joking.

96
00:05:13,729 --> 00:05:14,856
Let's hurry up and go back inside.

97
00:05:15,164 --> 00:05:17,164
We need to get back
and prepare for the meeting.

98
00:05:24,818 --> 00:05:26,621
We should eat lunch too. Let's go.

99
00:05:27,844 --> 00:05:30,560
No. I'm not hungry, so you go ahead.

100
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:33,533
You said you were meeting someone earlier.
Did something happen?

101
00:05:34,139 --> 00:05:35,700
No. What could've happened?

102
00:05:40,918 --> 00:05:42,381
Okay, then. I'll be back.

103
00:05:42,781 --> 00:05:43,781
All right.

104
00:05:49,644 --> 00:05:50,644
Hello?

105
00:05:51,593 --> 00:05:53,677
Do you still not remember me?

106
00:05:54,573 --> 00:05:57,140
I heard
you've been desperately searching for me.

107
00:05:57,655 --> 00:06:01,155
Then why did you bolt
the moment you saw me?

108
00:06:01,731 --> 00:06:04,707
I'll contact you
after I set a new time and place. Goodbye.

109
00:06:19,031 --> 00:06:21,155
Looks like today isn't a good day.

110
00:06:21,732 --> 00:06:23,349
I'll come back again soon.

111
00:06:29,527 --> 00:06:31,360
Who on earth is that man?

112
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,833
I'm sorry, honey. I need to find out too.

113
00:06:59,757 --> 00:07:03,075
This must be the reconstructed image
of Madam's daughter.

114
00:07:04,636 --> 00:07:05,636
Wait.

115
00:07:06,689 --> 00:07:08,789
Why does she look so familiar?

116
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:11,933
I'm sure I've seen this face before.

117
00:07:13,876 --> 00:07:15,843
You scared me!

118
00:07:16,525 --> 00:07:18,925
Don't you know how to knock?

119
00:07:19,285 --> 00:07:21,533
You do this
every time you come into my room.

120
00:07:22,257 --> 00:07:23,257
What are you doing, Mom?

121
00:07:23,733 --> 00:07:24,900
Those aren't even your documents.

122
00:07:25,824 --> 00:07:28,715
Your dad asked me to find something.

123
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,187
That's what I'm looking for. Why?

124
00:07:30,412 --> 00:07:31,412
Really?

125
00:07:31,872 --> 00:07:34,032
Why does that sound fake?

126
00:07:34,348 --> 00:07:35,348
What?

127
00:07:35,348 --> 00:07:38,149
I mean, Min Ho's mom before,

128
00:07:38,149 --> 00:07:39,349
and now you too.

129
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:42,156
Why is everyone interested
in Dad's documents?

130
00:07:42,156 --> 00:07:43,528
Interested? Don't be ridiculous.

131
00:07:44,013 --> 00:07:45,171
- Where are you going?
- The studio.

132
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:48,529
The studio?
I thought you only went at night.

133
00:07:48,529 --> 00:07:49,762
No.

134
00:07:49,932 --> 00:07:52,064
We decided to use it freely from now on.

135
00:07:52,635 --> 00:07:55,856
Apparently, staying up all night
disrupts human hormones,

136
00:07:55,856 --> 00:07:57,952
reduces immunity and concentration,

137
00:07:58,300 --> 00:07:59,461
so she was being considerate.

138
00:08:00,132 --> 00:08:01,373
As expected of my writer.

139
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:03,700
"My writer?"

140
00:08:05,277 --> 00:08:08,765
Then I shall take my leave, Your Majesty.

141
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:10,763
Okay. Have a good time.

142
00:08:18,184 --> 00:08:19,184
Who could it be?

143
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,261
I know that face. I'm sure of it.

144
00:08:32,357 --> 00:08:34,925
What are you working so hard on?

145
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:38,176
I'm making flower pancakes.

146
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,152
Flower pancakes? All of a sudden?

147
00:08:40,995 --> 00:08:42,436
I'm making some for you,

148
00:08:42,436 --> 00:08:45,493
and I'm taking some
to Gyeol's landlord's house later.

149
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,261
You're going there again?

150
00:08:49,373 --> 00:08:52,040
I still haven't returned
the beef bone soup container.

151
00:08:52,665 --> 00:08:55,731
I made plenty of chicken soup,
so I thought I'd bring some over too.

152
00:08:56,541 --> 00:08:58,501
Can I come with you?

153
00:08:59,139 --> 00:09:01,312
I'd love that,

154
00:09:01,774 --> 00:09:04,528
but wouldn't it make
the landlord uncomfortable?

155
00:09:05,402 --> 00:09:08,909
I'll just drop off the container and food
and come right back.

156
00:09:09,657 --> 00:09:10,657
Okay, then.

157
00:09:12,661 --> 00:09:14,013
How beautiful.

158
00:09:15,491 --> 00:09:16,491
These flower pancakes...

159
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,667
Yeon Sun loved them.

160
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:23,933
On days when the diner was closed,

161
00:09:25,304 --> 00:09:29,171
I'd go pick azalea petals in the mountains
and make them for her.

162
00:09:32,106 --> 00:09:35,273
She'd munch on them so happily.

163
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:41,700
She had such big, beautiful eyes.

164
00:09:42,883 --> 00:09:43,883
Yeon Sun...

165
00:09:44,596 --> 00:09:47,152
Here, try one.

166
00:09:48,449 --> 00:09:50,387
I don't know if it'll taste the same.

167
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:56,992
This is suffocating.

168
00:09:57,585 --> 00:09:59,568
It's not like I'm in prison.

169
00:09:59,768 --> 00:10:02,176
Why is she in the kitchen all day?

170
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,033
I'm going crazy.

171
00:10:06,321 --> 00:10:08,632
Su Jeong, can I come in?

172
00:10:15,723 --> 00:10:17,040
Are you feeling very sick?

173
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:18,576
Well...

174
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:20,984
I think I'm coming down with a cold.

175
00:10:22,981 --> 00:10:23,997
Did you take any medicine?

176
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:26,800
Not yet. I was just about to.

177
00:10:27,216 --> 00:10:30,352
You skipped breakfast. You shouldn't
take medicine on an empty stomach.

178
00:10:31,321 --> 00:10:32,640
Should I make you some rice porridge?

179
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,160
No, it's okay.

180
00:10:35,196 --> 00:10:38,596
I smelled the chicken soup earlier.

181
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:42,333
I'll eat some later
once I feel better, Mother.

182
00:10:42,589 --> 00:10:44,539
All right. Do that.

183
00:10:45,219 --> 00:10:46,800
I'm heading to Gyeol's landlord's house...

184
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:50,648
to return the container,
so make sure you eat.

185
00:10:50,811 --> 00:10:53,579
What, Mother? You're going where?

186
00:10:55,568 --> 00:10:58,037
Gyeol's landlord's house. What's wrong?

187
00:10:58,132 --> 00:11:00,768
Mother, I'll take it. I'll do it.

188
00:11:01,097 --> 00:11:04,056
It's fine. You said you're feeling sick.

189
00:11:04,432 --> 00:11:05,532
Just focus on getting better.

190
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:14,389
I'm going crazy. What do I do?

191
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:22,707
Honey.

192
00:11:23,452 --> 00:11:25,125
She's going there again?

193
00:11:25,327 --> 00:11:28,237
Your company is important and all,

194
00:11:28,237 --> 00:11:29,637
but are you really going to sit back
and do nothing?

195
00:11:29,941 --> 00:11:31,768
It's not like I'm doing nothing.

196
00:11:32,152 --> 00:11:35,763
I'm in the middle of preparing documents
to fire Mr. Cho.

197
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,000
What documents?

198
00:11:37,644 --> 00:11:40,788
He said he'd resign
if I gave him a valid reason,

199
00:11:40,788 --> 00:11:42,856
so I'm gathering every valid reason...

200
00:11:43,229 --> 00:11:44,771
I can find.

201
00:11:45,452 --> 00:11:48,152
And what are you doing?

202
00:11:48,253 --> 00:11:51,091
Me? Even if I wanted to do something,

203
00:11:51,091 --> 00:11:54,027
Mother's been in the kitchen all morning.

204
00:11:54,345 --> 00:11:56,323
I haven't even had breakfast yet.

205
00:11:59,772 --> 00:12:03,323
Honey, my blood sugar's crashing.
My hands are shaking.

206
00:12:03,815 --> 00:12:07,181
Crystal,
try being a little bolder for once.

207
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:09,899
Is keeping a poker face really that hard?

208
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:12,345
It's all because you can't control
your expression.

209
00:12:12,345 --> 00:12:13,563
Just because of that one thing,

210
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,376
you've skipped entire meals.
What kind of madness is this?

211
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:21,567
Okay. Mother is leaving soon.

212
00:12:21,848 --> 00:12:24,800
I'll eat first
and then figure something out.

213
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,563
All right. But when you eat,

214
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:28,139
eat boldly, okay?

215
00:12:28,386 --> 00:12:29,586
Okay. Good luck.

216
00:12:29,586 --> 00:12:30,586
Honey.

217
00:12:30,933 --> 00:12:33,773
Mr. Cho is one thing,

218
00:12:33,773 --> 00:12:36,427
but we need a way
to split up Gyeol and that girl too.

219
00:12:37,639 --> 00:12:40,576
No. Leave that to me.

220
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:45,161
You'll split them up? How?

221
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:48,683
With the oldest and most reliable method
there is.

222
00:12:48,993 --> 00:12:50,040
I'm hanging up, honey.

223
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:55,013
Yes. That's the method I'm using.

224
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,800
It's the one I'm best at.

225
00:12:58,575 --> 00:13:00,108
My Crystal is so transparent.

226
00:13:03,533 --> 00:13:06,100
(101 Reasons
Why Cho Seong Jun Should Resign)

227
00:13:10,444 --> 00:13:12,203
Talking back, 193 times.

228
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:14,700
Showing off, 365 times.

229
00:13:15,492 --> 00:13:16,592
This one really annoys me.

230
00:13:17,057 --> 00:13:19,224
Calling me "Ko Dae Chi," 15 times.

231
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,739
Forgetting to turn on
the heated seat, 11 times.

232
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,067
That's what made my hemorrhoids worse.

233
00:13:25,014 --> 00:13:28,018
The problem
is whether this will actually work.

234
00:13:28,018 --> 00:13:29,118
Right.

235
00:13:31,917 --> 00:13:34,707
Look at you.

236
00:13:35,077 --> 00:13:37,885
This alone is already a valid reason.

237
00:13:38,239 --> 00:13:41,321
Coming in right after knocking
without even waiting for me to respond.

238
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:42,321
Wait a second. What's this?

239
00:13:42,654 --> 00:13:44,523
One more count of poor attitude.

240
00:13:46,513 --> 00:13:50,469
Have you finished reviewing the documents
for the second round of the competition?

241
00:13:51,011 --> 00:13:52,911
The report has to be submitted
to the Chairman's office today.

242
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:54,100
The second round...

243
00:13:54,539 --> 00:13:56,539
The documents for the second round?
Hold on.

244
00:13:58,737 --> 00:14:01,170
I've been so busy
that I haven't reviewed these yet.

245
00:14:01,369 --> 00:14:02,837
All right. I'll do it now.

246
00:14:03,299 --> 00:14:05,605
Yes, please review them
and approve them right away.

247
00:14:05,944 --> 00:14:07,888
Yeah, sure. I will.

248
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:13,323
See? Even now.

249
00:14:13,323 --> 00:14:16,523
It's hard to tell who's the CEO
and who's the assistant.

250
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,700
Why do you keep giving me orders?

251
00:14:20,736 --> 00:14:21,992
One more count of showing off.

252
00:14:22,243 --> 00:14:24,488
That makes it 366 times.

253
00:14:25,383 --> 00:14:27,461
Please review them
and call me when you're done.

254
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:32,648
What is this?

255
00:14:33,433 --> 00:14:36,728
Does he not even care...

256
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:38,592
that I'm trying to fire him?

257
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,496
Right. The second round is important.

258
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Well...

259
00:14:45,535 --> 00:14:48,109
Min Ho absolutely has to beat Gyeol again
this time.

260
00:14:48,826 --> 00:14:50,493
Absolutely.

261
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:52,755
The blueprints look good.

262
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:56,332
As for the sports robot project,

263
00:14:56,332 --> 00:14:57,932
we received positive feedback.

264
00:14:58,476 --> 00:15:01,267
Though it won't be completed
by the second round,

265
00:15:02,552 --> 00:15:04,568
it looks like it can be deployed
in the field right away,

266
00:15:05,627 --> 00:15:07,171
so let's keep moving forward with it,
Mr. Han Ji Hun.

267
00:15:07,655 --> 00:15:10,339
Yes, understood. Thank you, Chief.

268
00:15:11,379 --> 00:15:13,379
The real issue is Team Two's strategy.

269
00:15:14,509 --> 00:15:16,661
Instead of overwhelming manpower
or superior technology,

270
00:15:16,928 --> 00:15:19,429
we need a unique strategy...

271
00:15:19,429 --> 00:15:20,779
that can genuinely connect with seniors.

272
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,500
These are the survey questions
for seniors.

273
00:15:23,732 --> 00:15:24,832
Please review them.

274
00:15:26,013 --> 00:15:27,313
Did you post them in the group chat too?

275
00:15:27,979 --> 00:15:31,548
Not yet. I wanted your approval first.

276
00:15:31,548 --> 00:15:34,181
Then post them right away.
Why is everyone moving so slowly?

277
00:15:34,483 --> 00:15:36,500
Have you forgotten the second round
is right around the corner?

278
00:15:38,024 --> 00:15:39,283
Should we take a short break?

279
00:15:39,632 --> 00:15:40,800
Could you get us some snacks?

280
00:15:41,206 --> 00:15:43,091
- Yes, understood.
- We'll be right back.

281
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:52,669
Seo Seung Ri,
why are you being so impatient?

282
00:15:53,116 --> 00:15:55,349
We're doing well.
What are you worried about?

283
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:58,651
We're doing well? Based on what?

284
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,355
What's gotten into you?

285
00:16:00,759 --> 00:16:03,359
You getting emotional like this
makes me even more anxious.

286
00:16:04,048 --> 00:16:06,275
Isn't rational
and logical decision-making...

287
00:16:06,567 --> 00:16:07,567
your greatest strength?

288
00:16:08,711 --> 00:16:10,267
Let's stay level-headed, okay?

289
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:13,475
I'm going to get some air.

290
00:16:23,146 --> 00:16:25,285
Hello, Mom. What?

291
00:16:27,133 --> 00:16:29,128
Why would you want
Cho Eun Ae's phone number?

292
00:16:29,557 --> 00:16:32,064
I have something to ask her.
Just text it to me.

293
00:16:33,285 --> 00:16:34,285
Okay.

294
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:51,499
What is it?
I was right in the zone, working.

295
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,613
Why did you drag me up to the rooftop?

296
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:56,537
Work is important, but if you keep staring
at a monitor all day,

297
00:16:56,537 --> 00:16:58,376
you'll get tech neck
and look like a turtle.

298
00:16:58,964 --> 00:17:00,237
Like a turtle? Please.

299
00:17:00,429 --> 00:17:03,379
I'm a rabbit. A hopping rabbit.

300
00:17:04,912 --> 00:17:07,221
All right, then, Miss Rabbit, follow me.

301
00:17:07,373 --> 00:17:08,373
Start with your neck.

302
00:17:09,049 --> 00:17:11,397
One, two, three, four,

303
00:17:11,397 --> 00:17:13,165
five, six, seven, eight.

304
00:17:13,165 --> 00:17:16,597
Left arm. One, two, three, four,

305
00:17:16,789 --> 00:17:18,477
five, six, seven, eight.

306
00:17:18,477 --> 00:17:21,560
Now the right arm. One, two, three, four,

307
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,593
five, six, seven... Hold on.

308
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,333
Hello?

309
00:17:29,091 --> 00:17:31,600
Right now? Okay.

310
00:17:33,794 --> 00:17:36,843
I'm heading to General Affairs,
so finish your stretches and come down.

311
00:17:37,055 --> 00:17:38,853
Do them for at least ten minutes, okay?

312
00:17:38,853 --> 00:17:40,037
Okay. See you later.

313
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:43,733
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

314
00:17:45,601 --> 00:17:46,601
Manager.

315
00:17:49,781 --> 00:17:52,581
Are you always that easy?

316
00:17:52,932 --> 00:17:54,832
Sorry? Easy in what way?

317
00:17:55,384 --> 00:17:56,947
Everything you do.

318
00:17:58,468 --> 00:17:59,765
I was surprised.

319
00:18:00,178 --> 00:18:02,778
You even called Madam "Grandma."

320
00:18:04,072 --> 00:18:06,436
I've lived under the same roof as her
for over ten years,

321
00:18:06,436 --> 00:18:08,592
and I've never once called her that.

322
00:18:09,476 --> 00:18:10,952
That's because when I first met Grandma...

323
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:14,600
I mean, when I first met her,
I didn't know who she was.

324
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:16,245
I've called her Grandma ever since.

325
00:18:16,941 --> 00:18:18,989
Is that the wrong way to address her?

326
00:18:19,377 --> 00:18:22,795
Once you found out who she was,
you should've corrected it.

327
00:18:24,204 --> 00:18:26,741
I don't really understand
why that's a problem.

328
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:31,925
I heard Team Manager
rejected your confession.

329
00:18:34,365 --> 00:18:36,651
Even after being rejected,

330
00:18:37,139 --> 00:18:40,369
you keep sticking by his side
and acting like this...

331
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:43,395
Don't you think
you're being a little too harsh?

332
00:18:46,220 --> 00:18:47,420
I'm being harsh?

333
00:18:48,462 --> 00:18:50,989
You're the one staying glued to his side
under the excuse of work...

334
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:54,875
and shaking up the feelings
of someone who already rejected you.

335
00:19:03,970 --> 00:19:04,970
Hello?

336
00:19:05,824 --> 00:19:08,709
Yes? Okay, I'm coming now.

337
00:19:12,684 --> 00:19:14,256
I have somewhere I need to be.

338
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,000
Let's continue this another time.

339
00:19:34,915 --> 00:19:38,509
No matter how strong genetics are,
how can they be this...

340
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Sorry?

341
00:19:42,721 --> 00:19:43,721
Never mind.

342
00:19:52,332 --> 00:19:53,432
What's this?

343
00:19:53,890 --> 00:19:55,057
Playing innocent, are we?

344
00:19:55,868 --> 00:19:57,435
You really don't know what this is?

345
00:19:59,065 --> 00:20:02,173
It's not a check or anything, is it?

346
00:20:02,482 --> 00:20:04,680
- What?
- I've seen it a lot in dramas.

347
00:20:05,054 --> 00:20:08,509
The rich wife says, "Take this and leave."

348
00:20:09,655 --> 00:20:11,059
But obviously, that's pretty outdated now.

349
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:12,300
What?

350
00:20:13,451 --> 00:20:14,747
Just check it first.

351
00:20:15,428 --> 00:20:17,211
Look at the amount before anything else.

352
00:20:18,388 --> 00:20:20,008
Do I really need to?

353
00:20:20,452 --> 00:20:22,392
I don't think you'd do something
like that, Mother.

354
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:24,033
What?

355
00:20:25,233 --> 00:20:27,400
Are you trying to get ahead of me already?

356
00:20:28,235 --> 00:20:30,667
I've jumped over people...

357
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,507
much craftier than you. What's with you?

358
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:39,323
Fine. I'll get straight to the point.

359
00:20:41,155 --> 00:20:43,392
Break up with Gyeol immediately.

360
00:20:44,648 --> 00:20:45,648
Mother.

361
00:20:46,109 --> 00:20:47,795
What? "Mother?"

362
00:20:49,829 --> 00:20:51,096
How ridiculous.

363
00:20:51,953 --> 00:20:53,586
I don't remember giving birth
to a daughter like you.

364
00:20:54,185 --> 00:20:56,101
Who do you think you're calling "Mother?"

365
00:20:57,381 --> 00:21:00,920
Ji Seon, where are you right now?

366
00:21:01,437 --> 00:21:02,829
Let's meet.

367
00:21:04,359 --> 00:21:06,717
Really? Okay, I'll wait.

368
00:21:08,875 --> 00:21:12,589
Good. That's a relief. Hold on.

369
00:21:13,604 --> 00:21:17,347
Cho Rong, could you pick up Bit Na
from daycare for me?

370
00:21:17,347 --> 00:21:18,893
Yes, of course.

371
00:21:19,052 --> 00:21:20,635
What's going on?

372
00:21:21,161 --> 00:21:23,392
Bit Na's mom is coming over later.

373
00:21:23,764 --> 00:21:26,341
I want to be home waiting
so we don't miss each other.

374
00:21:26,341 --> 00:21:29,581
Really?
Do you know what she wants to talk about?

375
00:21:29,879 --> 00:21:33,107
I'll find out when she gets here,
but I'll do my best to change her mind.

376
00:21:33,553 --> 00:21:36,885
That's great. Bit Na will be thrilled
when she hears her mom is coming.

377
00:21:37,346 --> 00:21:38,365
No, Cho Rong.

378
00:21:38,935 --> 00:21:41,400
Don't tell Bit Na about her mom.

379
00:21:41,620 --> 00:21:43,120
I'll talk to her first,

380
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:45,529
and if I think it's okay for them to meet,
then I'll call Bit Na.

381
00:21:45,529 --> 00:21:47,275
Keep her with you
for a little while longer, okay?

382
00:21:47,275 --> 00:21:48,375
Okay. I will.

383
00:21:49,028 --> 00:21:50,028
I'll get going.

384
00:21:50,148 --> 00:21:51,437
Thanks, Cho Rong.

385
00:21:51,678 --> 00:21:54,888
I think you're too nervous, Yeon Ja.

386
00:21:55,115 --> 00:21:58,120
Try to calm yourself down...

387
00:21:58,120 --> 00:21:59,501
and speak gently, okay?

388
00:21:59,501 --> 00:22:01,240
Yes, I will.

389
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:03,152
- I should get going too.
- All right.

390
00:22:04,632 --> 00:22:07,197
Children are your undoing.

391
00:22:08,253 --> 00:22:12,320
Money is your undoing,
and love is your undoing too.

392
00:22:12,776 --> 00:22:16,179
I'm sorry, but I don't really need money.

393
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:19,273
I should get back to the meeting now.

394
00:22:19,632 --> 00:22:21,659
This is unbelievable. Look.

395
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:25,915
Do you even know how much is in here?

396
00:22:28,904 --> 00:22:31,533
No. How much did you put in it?

397
00:22:32,144 --> 00:22:33,144
One.

398
00:22:33,594 --> 00:22:36,608
One? That's way too weak.

399
00:22:36,888 --> 00:22:38,317
Maybe if it were a hundred.

400
00:22:38,488 --> 00:22:40,896
What did you just say? This little...

401
00:22:48,327 --> 00:22:49,781
- Min Ho.
- Chief.

402
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,700
I'm sorry, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

403
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,144
Let me apologize on her behalf.
You should go.

404
00:22:57,133 --> 00:23:00,261
Okay. Then I'll really be going.

405
00:23:00,670 --> 00:23:01,670
Take care.

406
00:23:03,573 --> 00:23:05,084
What's with her?

407
00:23:05,084 --> 00:23:06,751
Seriously, what kind of person is that?

408
00:23:07,126 --> 00:23:09,526
Does she have any idea
how much is in here?

409
00:23:10,433 --> 00:23:12,187
What are you doing here, Mom?

410
00:23:12,187 --> 00:23:15,019
What do you think?
I told her to stay away from Gyeol.

411
00:23:15,019 --> 00:23:16,019
Why?

412
00:23:16,381 --> 00:23:18,499
Since when did you ever care about Gyeol?

413
00:23:18,765 --> 00:23:20,245
- What?
- A lot of people...

414
00:23:20,245 --> 00:23:21,272
from our company come here.

415
00:23:21,741 --> 00:23:22,741
What if Grandpa finds out...

416
00:23:22,968 --> 00:23:24,896
you're doing this here?

417
00:23:25,341 --> 00:23:27,155
Says the one who...

418
00:23:27,389 --> 00:23:29,556
made that ridiculous public proposal
in the company lobby.

419
00:23:30,061 --> 00:23:32,272
Fine. We'll discuss the details at home.

420
00:23:32,517 --> 00:23:34,120
- Let's go.
- Forget it. Let go.

421
00:23:35,014 --> 00:23:37,093
I'm going to your office
and having a word with your father.

422
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:46,787
How have you been?
Where have you been all this time?

423
00:23:48,546 --> 00:23:49,661
I'm sorry, Mother.

424
00:23:50,433 --> 00:23:53,749
I've been flying long-haul routes
in South America,

425
00:23:54,771 --> 00:23:56,333
so I couldn't contact you.

426
00:23:56,663 --> 00:23:58,709
You've gotten so thin.

427
00:24:00,148 --> 00:24:02,947
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

428
00:24:02,947 --> 00:24:04,315
I'm so, so sorry.

429
00:24:05,653 --> 00:24:07,056
No, Mother.

430
00:24:07,622 --> 00:24:09,109
This is all my fault.

431
00:24:09,308 --> 00:24:11,885
How can you be apologizing to me?

432
00:24:12,307 --> 00:24:15,392
No. I know exactly...

433
00:24:15,392 --> 00:24:16,888
how you got caught up in that scam.

434
00:24:17,784 --> 00:24:21,351
Still, thank you so much for coming.

435
00:24:22,464 --> 00:24:23,464
Mother.

436
00:24:24,047 --> 00:24:26,632
I have some documents
I need to give Eun Hyeong,

437
00:24:27,987 --> 00:24:31,173
but because of my flight schedule,
I won't be able to see him myself.

438
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:34,013
Could you please...

439
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:36,624
give these to Eun Hyeong?

440
00:24:39,016 --> 00:24:40,016
What's this?

441
00:24:44,833 --> 00:24:49,300
(Agreement on Child Custody
and Parental Rights)

442
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,200
Ji Seon.

443
00:24:57,079 --> 00:25:00,704
I'll give it to her and come right away,
so go wait inside the restaurant.

444
00:25:02,515 --> 00:25:04,824
It's heavy. Let me carry it in for you.

445
00:25:05,217 --> 00:25:07,581
I'm still strong enough for this.

446
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:09,100
It's heavy.

447
00:25:09,678 --> 00:25:10,678
I'll get the door.

448
00:25:15,261 --> 00:25:16,653
You don't mean...

449
00:25:17,201 --> 00:25:22,037
you're giving up custody of Bit Na?

450
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:25,147
Mother, that's not it.

451
00:25:25,537 --> 00:25:27,761
Please change your mind, Ji Seon.

452
00:25:27,761 --> 00:25:30,168
We'll pay off the debt together.

453
00:25:30,507 --> 00:25:32,931
How can you separate from your own child
because of money?

454
00:25:32,931 --> 00:25:34,269
Does that make any sense?

455
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:38,523
Mother, I'm not trying
to give up Bit Na completely.

456
00:25:39,628 --> 00:25:42,917
It's just that, right now,
I'm not in a position to raise her.

457
00:25:43,852 --> 00:25:45,147
After thinking it over,

458
00:25:45,881 --> 00:25:49,348
I'm only transferring custody
to Eun Hyeong.

459
00:25:51,208 --> 00:25:53,077
Mother, I have to go.

460
00:25:53,669 --> 00:25:55,083
I have to get to work.

461
00:25:55,083 --> 00:25:56,477
You came all the way here,

462
00:25:56,477 --> 00:25:58,427
and you're leaving without seeing Bit Na?

463
00:25:58,669 --> 00:26:01,173
How can you do that? You're her mom!

464
00:26:01,985 --> 00:26:04,869
Do you think I want to leave
without seeing her?

465
00:26:05,889 --> 00:26:07,232
If I want to pay off the debt,

466
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,816
I have to keep working.

467
00:26:12,533 --> 00:26:15,333
Once I've paid off
at least some of the urgent debt,

468
00:26:16,285 --> 00:26:17,553
I'll come back.

469
00:26:17,553 --> 00:26:18,952
By then, it'll be too late!

470
00:26:20,792 --> 00:26:21,825
Mother.

471
00:26:26,631 --> 00:26:27,631
Is anyone there?

472
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,528
You think I'm supposed to believe that?

473
00:26:30,068 --> 00:26:32,591
You tell her you'll come get her soon
and ask her to wait,

474
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:33,824
but in the end, you won't come.

475
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:39,608
Why are you saying this?

476
00:26:40,088 --> 00:26:43,300
If you look at these papers,

477
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:45,949
you'll see that I've even applied
for visitation rights.

478
00:26:46,896 --> 00:26:48,645
My circumstances right now...

479
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:50,488
What circumstances?

480
00:26:50,488 --> 00:26:53,477
Do you know Bit Na went all the way back
to your old house by herself?

481
00:26:53,749 --> 00:26:56,237
She must've missed her mom terribly.

482
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:01,117
What? Bit Na went to our old house?

483
00:27:01,501 --> 00:27:03,599
Exactly. So don't go.

484
00:27:03,599 --> 00:27:05,799
Please, Ji Seon. Please.

485
00:27:06,083 --> 00:27:07,083
Well...

486
00:27:07,656 --> 00:27:10,885
Mother, I really have to get to work.

487
00:27:11,317 --> 00:27:14,301
Ji Seon, please.

488
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,640
Please, Ji Seon.

489
00:27:28,176 --> 00:27:29,424
Please don't go.

490
00:27:30,035 --> 00:27:31,794
A child abandoned by her mother...

491
00:27:31,794 --> 00:27:34,761
is as good as dead
for the rest of her life.

492
00:27:35,373 --> 00:27:37,579
If even the mother
who gave birth to her abandons her,

493
00:27:37,741 --> 00:27:39,012
where can she go,

494
00:27:39,012 --> 00:27:41,445
and how can she ever build a stable life?

495
00:27:42,733 --> 00:27:45,900
Mother, I'm really late. I have to go.

496
00:27:46,553 --> 00:27:49,003
Ji Seon. Bit Na's mom!

497
00:27:51,103 --> 00:27:52,803
What do I do?

498
00:28:00,533 --> 00:28:01,533
Ma'am.

499
00:28:20,933 --> 00:28:22,400
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
